  <section class="who-should-read-this">
    <h2 class="centered">Who Should Read This Book?</h2>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="quarter-page">
        <h3>Programmers</h3>
        <p>The most versatile programmers today are the "full stack developers", armies-of-one that can solve any and all problems facing online businesses. As the complexity of online marketing tools increases, business owners increasingly need the technical ability of programmer to implement server-side SEO, analytical tracking tools, API connections to paid advertising platforms etcetera. The programmers with these bonus skills therefore become indispensable to their employers and clients.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="quarter-page">
        <h3>Web Entrepreneurs</h3>
        <p>The main reason web businesses fail is because they can't get enough traffic. They build and build, but no-one comes. That's why it's crucial to start your business with a clear idea of exactly where and how you will find your first thousand customers. This book will give you a roadmap of the most promising sources of traffic along with the techniques needed to convert these visitors into paying customers.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="quarter-page">
        <h3>Experienced Online Marketers</h3>
        <p>While not everything in this book will be new to the experienced online marketer, there sections that will tickle even the most experienced with fresh perspectives. In particular, this group of readers will enjoy the discussion of strategic principles for online advertising effectiveness and the breakdown of the most important variables in conversion optimisation.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="quarter-page">
        <h3>Anyone Who Needs to Self-Promote </h3>
        <p>
          Many of us want attention for reasons other than the pursuit of paying customers: We may wish to build a following for our personal brand as an author or musician, or we may want to promote a beloved political cause. Whatever your goal, this book will help you reach more people faster.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>

